parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The "Service Airbag" warning light is illuminated
the airbag warning light is on
the passenger airbag is not deploying
the airbag system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the dashboard can lead to shrapnel injuries in the event of an airbag deployment, and may also affect the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracks in the dashboard
particularly around the passenger airbag area
cracks in the dashboard that may cause shrapnel injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in repairing or replacing defective airbag systems can lead to continued risk of injury or death, and may also affect the resale value of the vehicle.
symptoms: Unavailability of parts
lack of communication from dealerships or manufacturers
delays in repair or replacement of defective airbag systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can create a safety hazard in the event of an accident, potentially causing shrapnel to be sent throughout the cabin, and may also affect the deployment of airbags.
symptoms: Cracks in the dashboard
particularly around the passenger airbag and instrument cluster
cracks that appear suddenly
cracks that spread over time
loud pops or noises coming from the dashboard area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose door panel can create a safety hazard in the event of an emergency, making it difficult to open the door, and may also cause damage to the door frame.
symptoms: Door panel becomes loose over time
catches on the inside of the door frame
making it difficult to open the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the vehicle to hesitate, stall, or experience harsh shifting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates
stalls
or experiences harsh shifting
power door locks begin cycling open and closed
intermittent chime operation
gauges fluctuate
traction control and stabilitrak turn off
and service traction control and service stabilitrak messages appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, experience power loss, or have faulty electrical components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
experiences power loss
faulty electrical components
instrument panel lights blink on and off
speedometer and tachometer gauges fluctuate
air bag and transmission indicators illuminate
and engine seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, experience power loss, or have faulty electrical components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
experiences power loss
faulty electrical components
and the ignition switch can be pulled out after starting the ignition and with it running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to not lock or unlock, which can be a safety concern in the event of an accident or a security concern.
symptoms: The power door locks won't lock and unlock
the driver's door lock actuator works intermittently
and the door locks do not always lock or unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Chassis Electronic Control Module Internal Contamination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The contamination of the chassis electronic control module can cause the vehicle to stall, experience power loss, or have faulty electrical components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
experiences power loss
faulty electrical components
and the speedometer and tachometer gauges fluctuate.
